==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monometallism
<hw>Mon`o*met"al*lism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Mono-</ets> + <ets>metal</ets>.]</ety> <def>The legalized use
of one metal only, as gold, or silver, in the standard currency of a
country, or as a standard of money values. See
<er>Bimetallism</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monometallist</ent>⟦br⟧
